\section*{Reflective Introduction}
Provide a one-page reflective introduction demonstrating how you have met the learning outcomes. Include a critical review of how your work relates to engineering, and signpost the assignment sections that showcase this knowledge.

\newpage

\section*{Problem 1: Regression (Concrete)}
\subsection*{Data Preparation and Transformation}
Discuss the process of loading the concrete data and transforming it, using water-cement and water-binder ratios, to linearize the relationship between age and compressive strength.

\subsection*{First Regression Analysis}
Explain and present results from the first regression, showing plots of $b_0$ and $b_1$ versus $\log(\text{Age})$. Provide commentary on the linearity of these relationships.

\subsection*{Second Regression Analysis}
Discuss the second regression that models $b_0$ and $b_1$ as functions of age. Show scatter plots for Age 14, and compare models using estimated versus calculated parameters.

\subsection*{Model Performance}
Assess the residuals for transformed and raw data on training and testing sets. Present R-squared values in a table and discuss any patterns in performance and recommendations for improvement.

\newpage

\section*{Problem 2: Statistics (Wind Turbine SCADA Analysis)}
\subsection*{Data Summary and Initial Scatter Plots}
Provide a brief summary of the SCADA data. Include scatter plots of wind speed versus energy production for both datasets, and hypothesize potential differences between them.

\subsection*{Binning Analysis}
Using wind speed bins, compute and plot the mean, standard deviation, and 95\% confidence intervals for each bin. Plot and discuss results, including any insights on turbine performance.

\newpage

